class Solution {
public:
    int findKthLargest(vector<int>& nums, int k) 
    {
        priority_queue<int,vector<int>,greater<int>> minheap;
        for(auto& ele:nums)
        {
            minheap.push(ele);
            if(minheap.size()>k) minheap.pop();
        }
        return minheap.top();
    }
};

Time Complexity: O(n log k)

- Traverse all n elements.
- Each insertion into the min-heap of size at most k takes O(log k).
- If heap size exceeds k, one deletion is performed, which also takes O(log k).
- Therefore, total time = O(n log k).

Space Complexity: O(k)

- The min-heap stores at most k elements.
